Description: # exchange_trade_importer: A service to load cryptocurrency exchange trades
        
        ## Installation Guide: What do you need
        
        Docker with MongoDB
        Schema cryp
        Collection trades created
        poetry installed
        "poetry install" command executed
        
        ## Service architecture: What, where, how and maybe why
        
        All code can be found in src folder, and the data to be loaded in storage folder, both at BASE location: ./exchange_trade_importer
        Service dependencies are at BASE/pyproject.toml
        Service can be used from command line with the following instruction: poetry run exchange_trade_importer -d
        This 
        
        ## Database definition
        
        MongoDB database has one schema: cryp
        
        The schema has one collection: trades
        
        Each trades record is composed of the following fields and the fields have the following types:
        
            _id: ObjectId
            isodate: ISODate
            date: String
            market: String 
            type: String [SELL, BUY]
            price: String
            amount: String
            total: String
            fee: String
            fee_coin: String
            primary_coin: Dict Object
                short_name: String
                long_name: String
            secondary_coin: Dict Object
                short_name: String
                long_name: String
            source: String
            description: String
            record_key: String
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
Requires-Python: >=3.7
